<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  6. Word has it that Hareq doesn't attend any raids that he doesn't lead. Is this true ? I think not. Did I not go to Kael and help Malleolus ? How about when I helped Holt on his KK raid ? Zenknight's raid in Kithicor Forrest?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not sure where this is coming from. I talk to everyone and am at every event, and have never heard anything like this uttered. This is a ridicoulous assertion, you do more than your share for the SGA. On a side note: we are not Uber_guild_01, and do not require any attendance to any raid regardless of who you are. Raids are to be fun in the SGA, not a job.<br>
<br>
If you look back through the message board there have been no less than 8 posts regarding membership, not 2. I have personally spoken to officers in these guilds ingame, on msgboards, and through emails. I encourage everyone in the SGA to lookout for the good of the organization, this is your responsibility and it will further all of us by your commitment.<br>
<br>
As for leading raids you are right. It's a big job. I spent 13 straight hours Sunday in tell hell, dealing with every single issue that came up at both raids, and I wasn't the raid leader, so I can imagine. When I logged off I was physically and mentally drained, and I had 0 want to play. I have yet to log Bamil back on from that day, and probably won't until this weekend. Having an official title with some type of leadership stigma attached to it can be a big job. I thank the GL's and officers of our guilds for doing a tremendous job.<br>
<br>
Landy,<br>
<br>
I agree with everything you have said. This is my concern as well. Adding guilds and meeting new friends should be a great experience, however there are precautions to take. I like our organization to this point, and personally opt for a slow expansion rather than a constant influx of change. If we are going to do things we need to do them right.<br>
<br>
Anyhow... all that being said, you will be seeing a new member in the SGA shortly. I too think this is an exciting time for us all.<br>
