I feel that we need to have not raids to gain loot, but instead scheduled raids to gain experience. Lets face it there are really only two things in this game that count and thats exp and loot. The rest is just emotional mumbo jumbo. So lets get some Icewell raids going and get some hole Raids going. I would personally like to see a new section on the message board for EXP-GROUPS. I sat last night in Karnors (that place is way to camped) and realized that I wasn't getting any exp here and that I wasn't around the people that I wanted to be around, namely the SGA members. So I logged off a very unsatisfied cleric. If we had a daily schedule just of people saying &quot;I am going to be at this place tonight getting exp, anyone want to join?&quot; then I wouldn't have been stuck in the dilema I was last night. <br>
<br>
Then again, perhaps that isn't the thing to do?<br>
I don't know the real solution of how to get with you guys, but I simply would like to group more with the SGA members. I am getting kind of burned out on this night after night of thrown together groups.<br>
